==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blanchard lathe
<hw>Blan"chard lathe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After Thomas
<etsep>Blanchard</etsep>, American inventor.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<def>A kind of wood-turning lathe for making noncircular and irregular
forms, as felloes, gun stocks, lasts, spokes, etc., after a given
pattern. The pattern and work rotate on parallel spindles in the same
direction with the same speed, and the work is shaped by a rapidly
rotating cutter whose position is varied by the pattern acting as a cam
upon a follower wheel traversing slowly along the pattern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blancher</ent>⟦br⟧
